5
6 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Enforcement -- damages. (1) A violation of [section 1] is a violation of
7 30-14-103.
8 (2) The department of justice may bring an action to restrain any unlawful act pursuant to the
9 provisions of Title 30, chapter 14, part 1.
10 (3) An individual whose electronic consumer product personally owned property has a kill switch
11 activated in violation of [section 1] may bring an action pursuant to 30-14-133, except that:
12 (a) the individual needs to show only a violation of [section 1] for that individual’s electronic
13 consumer product personally owned property and is not required to show any other ascertainable loss of
14 money or property; and
15 (b) the individual is entitled to statutory damages of $10,000 for each violation of [section 1] in
16 addition to any other damages or monetary award pursuant to 30-14-133.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 and 2] are intended to be codified
19 as a new part in Title 30, chapter 14, and the provisions of Title 30, chapter 14, apply to [sections 1 and 2].
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective October 1, 2025.
